{
  "texts": [
    "This issue is commonly addressed by inserting selection functionality into CAs.",
    "Various approaches, including the integration of transistors with memristors in a onetransistor one-memristor (1T1M) configureation 31, [36] [37] [38] [39], and the incorporating of selector devices such as ovonic threshold switching [40] [41] [42], mixed ionic-electronic conductors 43, and field-assisted super-linear threshold switching devices 44 in a one-selector one-memristor (1S1M) configuration have been explored.",
    "However, integrating transistors in the 1T1M configuration can result in area overhead issues, and integrating selectors in the 1S1M configuration poses practical and compatibility challenges for memristors.",
    "Self-rectifying memristors (SRMs) have emerged as a promising solution to overcome these challenges.",
    "They possess inherent selection functionality, which allows them to effectively suppress sneak currents and enable accurate and efficient VMM operations in CAs."
  ]
}